race.comment: SPARKINGLY (6) impressed when fresh from a 13-month spell last start over 1000m at Canberra, working home in good style to get up for second. Will take a lot from that run and over a slightly longer trip out of gate one he looks very hard to stop. TELEGRAPH (8) was outclassed last time out in a quality sprint over 1200m here. Last raced at this level three back when runner-up at Tuncurry under the same weight. Key contender based on that performance. GET SOME FUN (9) returns from a 20-week spell. Raced well last time in work largely in town or at the provincials. Loves this circuit so a bright return will come as no surprise. BUCK PHAROAH (1) comes here off a last start second in open company over 1250m at Taree. Faces a far easier assignment today but 65kgs is a decent steadier. CANNY PROSPECT (5) is up in grade but won impressively here last start over 1000m. Cannot be ruled out.
